	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">My Isengard Orcs Deck (shadow only)</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><table width='50' border='0' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='0'><tr><td background='/lotr/gfx/5star.gif'><img src='/lotr/gfx/trans.gif' width='1' height='25'></td></tr></table><font size=1>(5.00)</font> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=25296">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=7358">Third "Third Angel" Angel</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=7358&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> I would like some help with Isengard Orcs... Orcs, Balrog, and Enquea.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> August 30, 2002</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Sites that matter:<br>
<br>
Site 4: <a href="javascript:card_browser(227)">Pass of Caradhras</a> (gets <a href="javascript:card_browser(953)">Wizard Storm</a> out)<br>
Site 5: The only one (required to get balrog out -6)<br>
Site 6: Caras Galadhon (best site in the game for Isengard orcs)<br>
Site 7: Wilderland OR Confluence(should I do anti-archery? or anti-Allies?)<br>
<br>
Shadow Cards: (34)<br>
<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(843)">The Balrog, Durin&#39;s Bane</a> (6)<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(960)">Dark Places</a> x4 (1)<br>
<br>
Ulaire Enquea , Lieutenant of Morgul x2 (6)<br>
<br>
Saruman, Servant of the Eye x4 (4)<br>
A Fel Voice on the Air x2 (1)<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(953)">Wizard Storm</a> (2, 0)<br>
<br>
Isengard Servant x3 (3)<br>
Isengard Warrior x2 (3)<br>
Isengard Shaman (1)<br>
Isengard Smith x2 (4)<br>
Isengard Worker (2)<br>
Orc Commander (6)<br>
Orc Overseer (5)<br>
<br>
Isengard Axe x3 (-1)<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(949)">No Business of Ours</a> x2 (0)<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(33)">Saruman&#39;s Power</a> (2)<br>
The Palantir of Orthanc (0)<br>
<br>
The Trees are Strong x2 (1)<br>
<br>
I want to put in:<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(33)">Saruman&#39;s Power</a> (a must, to take out betrayal of isengard)<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(36)">Spies of Saruman</a> x2 (need against archery decks)<br>
Trapped and Alone x2 (want against dwarf/weapons (like <a href="javascript:card_browser(256)">Gwemegil</a>, ranger sword, sword of boromir... etc))<br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> <br>
first off, I&#39;m not posting this to get high stars, so go ahead and give it 3, or 4... that&#39;s cool. I need help figuring out how to best play my isengard orcs. <br>
<br>
The Idea is to drop down Dark Places to boost balrog up... With one out, Balrog kills anyone str 9 or less... with three out he kills str 10 or less.<br>
<br>
all before site five is just getting wizard storm into the discard pile (site 4) and getting set up for a site 6 kill.<br>
<br>
site 5, balrog drops out, and if they do a double move you have extra twilight for the isenguard orcs. (if not that&#39;s cool too)<br>
<br>
basically unless they single move from 4-5-6 they will get chewed up by wizard storm, balrog, and the orcs.<br>
<br>
site 6, drop down orcs (hopefully alot) and hopefully they only have a few companions left after balrog kills off two =) and that leaves a few isengard orcs unassigned. which lets them live to the regroup phase (in which they can deal all their damage!)<br>
<br>
and whomever didn&#39;t die at site 6... can get taken out at site 7. (I&#39;m thinking anti-archery... but I&#39;m not sure... killing off their allies can make or break a deck... some help please)<br>
<br>
if they make it to site 9, I&#39;m toast, and they&#39;ve won... so I want to make sure I can take them out before site nine.<br>
<br>
I&#39;m new to the isenguard orcs thing, so I need some help as to how to play right.<br>
<br>
I play 4 sarumans, beacuse even with 1 or 2 orcs, saruman makes sure they live all the way into the regroup phase (or he deals the wounds for them when the companions exert to cancel his assignment.)<br>
<br>
Plus with &#39;a fel voice on the air&#39; I can get a re-occuring wizard storm, which will hurt their companions if they try for a double or triple move, leaving the orcs a chance to finish the job.<br>
<br>
I got saruman&#39;s Power to take out &#39;betrayal of isengard&#39; which would really hurt this deck. I&#39;d like to put another one in, but still keep it down to 34 cards. (or less)<br>
<br>
also if you have any other ideas, they would help. (I&#39;m thinking of putting in the other cards listed... reasons written afterwards) and I don&#39;t know about &#39;can you protect me from yourself&#39;, it looks like a good card, but could be a wasted card slot... is it worth it? any help is appreciated.<br>
<br>
thanks,<br>
